{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "NMOS Transistor Intro",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "NMOS Transistor Intro",
    "description": "Your first MOSFET switch. Press the tact button: USB → 10kΩ → NMOS gate (west face at 90° rotation) turns the FET on. The load path is USB → T → 470Ω → red LED → drain (north), and source (south) → ground — no base current and no emitter resistor like the NPN lessons. The gate is voltage-driven; the LED current flows drain–source when the FET is on. Compare lesson 58 (same tact + LED layout, NPN with B/C/E) and lesson 72 (optical sensor). NMOS at 90°; LED at 90°."
  },
